place.name: WARREN
place.gazetteerText: WARREN, a parish in the district and county of Pembroke; 5 miles SSW of Pembroke r. station. Post town, Pembroke. Acres, 1,169. Real property, £1,029. Pop., 121. Houses, 18. The property is all in one estate. The living is a vicarage, united with St. Twinnell, in the diocese of St. David's. Value, £121.* Patrons, the Dean and Chapter of St. D. The church is old but good. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
